  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">Accretion disk size problem</h1>

    <p>The accretion disk size problem refers to the persistent finding that continuum reverberation lags suggest accretion disks are several times larger than predicted by standard thin-disk theory. Proposed explanations include diffuse emission contamination, non-standard disk structure, or reprocessing geometry complexities.</p>

    <ul>
      <li><WikiLink slug="pages/steyn_2026_continuum_reverberation" text="Steyn et al. (2026)" /></li>
    </ul>
  </main>
</Base>
